in the Brillouin zone

00:49:57.460 --> 00:50:03.250
a letter, a Greek
letter, or not.

00:50:03.250 --> 00:50:04.780
And then I went back to gamma.

00:50:04.780 --> 00:50:08.440
Here, I went to a point
we called L. And I--

00:50:08.440 --> 00:50:10.570
the way you do this is
you just, basically,

00:50:10.570 --> 00:50:13.600
go in a line from this
point to that point.

00:50:13.600 --> 00:50:17.470
And you plot the change
in the energy of each band

00:50:17.470 --> 00:50:20.770
as you go from point to
point in the Brillouin zone.

00:50:20.770 --> 00:50:23.770
