00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:56.970
So you see, when you
calculate the band structure,

00:54:56.970 --> 00:55:00.610
what you do is
you do two things.

00:55:00.610 --> 00:55:04.620
First, you converge the
wave function in density.

00:55:04.620 --> 00:55:08.640
First, you converge the
density at the k-points I input

00:55:08.640 --> 00:55:11.920
into the input.

00:55:11.920 --> 00:55:15.130
So if I have a 1-by-1-by-1
k-point density, well,

00:55:15.130 --> 00:55:17.897
that gives me some grid.

00:55:17.897 --> 00:55:19.980
That gives me some density
and some wave function.

00:55:22.510 --> 00:55:25.900
Now, then to calculate the band
structure, what the code does

00:55:25.900 --> 00:55:27.400
is it does a second step.

00:55:27.400 --> 00:55:29.410
It takes that converged density.

00:55:29.410 --> 00:55:31.750
And it cruises
around in k-space.

00:55:31.750 --> 00:55:33.880
And that's how it
plots this out.

00:55:33.880 --> 00:55:35.830
But it doesn't change
the density anymore.

00:55:35.830 --> 00:55:37.747
It doesn't change the
converged wave function.

00:55:37.747 --> 00:55:39.430
It just evaluates
it at all kinds

00:55:39.430 --> 00:55:41.540
of different points in k-space.

00:55:41.540 --> 00:55:43.500
So there's two steps.

00:55:43.500 --> 00:55:48.020
First, you converge the density
at some number of k-points.

00:55:48.020 --> 00:55:50.870
Then you cruise around
in the Brillouin zone

00:55:50.870 --> 00:55:52.490
with that density.

00:55:52.490 --> 00:55:54.710
And you evaluate your functions.

00:55:54.710 --> 00:55:59.060
And sure, the wrong
density will still

00:55:59.060 --> 00:56:01.820
wiggle as you move
around in k-space.

00:56:01.820 --> 00:56:03.140
It'll still wiggle.

00:56:03.140 --> 00:56:04.700
